OREON Motor Maintenance Manual

Scope: DC and AC drive motors used in conveyors, pumps, fans, and mill auxiliaries.

Normal operating envelope: winding temperature below 80 C, bearing housing temperature below 75 C,
vibration below 4.5 mm/s RMS, current below rated full-load current, and clean cooling passages.

Bearing wear indicators include rising vibration, grinding noise, drive-end temperature increase,
metallic particles in grease, axial looseness, and resonance near bearing defect frequencies.
Recommended response: inspect lubricant condition, confirm alignment, capture vibration spectrum,
replace affected bearing if raceway spalling is confirmed, and verify coupling balance.

Motor overload indicators include current above rated load, thermal rise, low insulation resistance,
repeated thermal trips, or driven equipment drag. Corrective actions include reducing load, checking
VFD parameters, measuring winding resistance, inspecting terminals, and inspecting the driven asset.

Cooling failure indicators include blocked fan guards, failed motor cooling fan, dust accumulation,
high ambient temperature, and reduced air velocity across the frame.
